description.@value: 第2巻：敦煌の千仏洞調査始まり、漢代長城の調査、漢代遺物の発見、さらに敦煌文書の発見について述べる。ついで瓜州から河西回廊の調査を概観し、天山南路のハミ・トルファン・カラシャール・クチャ・アクス・ヤルカンドを経てコータンの調査、さらにチベットを経てインドに帰還するまでを含む。

Vol. 2: Beginning with Stein’s visit to the Dunhuang’s Caves of the Thousand Buddhas, the narrative includes his investigations of the Han dynasty remains of the Great Wall as well as descriptions of how he came to discover the manuscripts at Dunhuang. He also describes his expedition from Guazhou to the Hexi Corridor in Gansu Province, then continuing via the Southern Tian Shan Mountain Route to Hami, Turfan, Karashahr, Kucha,Aksu, Yarkand, and Khotan. The narrative includes his final return to India via Tibet.
